## Basic Generic Syntax

### Function Declaration

```aria
// Single type parameter
fn identity<T>(value: T) -> T {
    return value;
}

// Multiple type parameters
fn pair<T, U>(first: T, second: U) -> (T, U) {
    return (first, second);
}
```

### Struct Declaration

```aria
// Generic struct
struct Box<T> {
    value: T
}

// Multiple type parameters
struct Pair<T, U> {
    first: T,
    second: U
}
```

### Enum Declaration

```aria
// Generic enum
enum Option<T> {
    Some(T),
    None
}

// Multiple type parameters
enum Result<T, E> {
    Ok(T),
    Err(E)
}
```

